matcher must be installed for the ctrlP plugin for vim to work properly:
  Follow instructions from: https://github.com/burke/matcher
  * clone
  * make
  * make install
  * Make sure to copy the matcher file from the build directory into ~/bin/

The mac and linux PS1 settings require the existance of ~/.git-completion.sh (included in /generic)

On Mac:
  - If using iterm2 make sure to change preferences > profiles > Terminal > Report Terminal Type to "xterm-256color"
